<br>
I do agree, though, that Moderators should behave in ways that set an example.  They, above all others, should be above reproach.  Their authority depends, in part, on the acceptance of that authority by the posters.  While it's not unusual for any board to have its crank, when a substantial number of posters, even if they're in the minority over all, believe the Moderation to be skewed or unfair, there may be a problem worth looking at more closely and addressed appropriately.<br>
<br>
